@node register "Registering AStart"
AStart is mailware. It is not crippled or limited in any way and why should it?

But you are strongly recommended to register AStart. If you register, you'll receive a personalized library with @{i}registered to... @{ui}in the legal status field.

I am also open for @{b}any@{ub} suggestions, so write if you think of anything new.
@endnode
@node bugs "Is your computer in danger?"
No, it will not format harddrives (I hope).

But anyway, here's what I have discovered:
ĚáMBench does not work correctly with GoForIt, the @{b}Enabled@{ub} and @{b}Disabled@{ub} folders' icons have to be deleted, because apparently MBench does not check if the object is a directory like the OS2.x (to delete them,@{" click Here " system "C:Delete QUIET SYS:WBStartup/WBStartup??(Dis|En)abled?.info"})
ĚáThe ENV->ENVArc option will probably @{b}erase@{ub} your old options if you select the option @{b}@{i}Use @{ui}@{ub}and the program saves the config in ENV:
Ěáthe configuration program does not look very nice on 640x256 and topaz/8
Ěáastart.library is not closed by the AStart command, because if its opencount will be 0 and the user will "flush" the memory, the data about astart and wbstartup mode would be erased, so it is not a bug, but is worth mentioning
Ěáafter installing every update, you'll have to save the prefs, because of the "compilation" process - may be fixed in the future versions.

Here's what I have discovered and got rid of:
ĚáGoForIt used to need newfmt.library, which it didn't use anyway (thanx Moszum)
ĚáWBStartup+ wasn't replaced by the installer, it is now

If you find any bugs, send an info about it to@{" me " link "contact"}.
@endnode
